text:
I have an older slow running mac book and am wondering; 
does overheating cause a CPU to slow down?
This would be a good test every six months to see how it progresses over time.

replies.text:
@scotttovey 
overheating causes a CPU to slow down, I owned a computer repair shop for 6 years, what I saw most, the first cause of a slow computer was malware / spyware, second most was dust and clogged heat sinks, third was dried heat sink compound .
Some times it would happen on a one year old computer, most the time it was after three years, some times they would last 5 years before needing the heat sink compound replaced .

@OverUnity7734 
My brother gave me a 2007 Mac book that is doing that.
I guess I'll have to take it apart and give it a cleaning; after I find where I put my thermal compound.
